Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.65,0:04:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even the message is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.95,0:04:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The message.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:04:56.70,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shining Finger."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.41,0:05:00.79,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,"I have new information regarding the time machine."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.71,0:05:03.75,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'd like to talk to you alone."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.47,0:05:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.68,0:05:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put your hands up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.40,0:05:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you people?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.20,0:05:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arc rewrite.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're planning to attack the lab and kidnap us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.54,0:05:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.25,0:05:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I've come from the future!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.88,0:05:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.09,0:05:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.05,0:05:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.84,0:05:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.13,0:05:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you with SERN?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.89,0:05:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rounder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.93,0:05:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rounder?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.85,0:06:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mission is to recover the IBN 5100.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.43,0:06:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who stole it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.69,0:06:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.69,0:06:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try tricking me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.73,0:06:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sent that D-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.77,0:06:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.94,0:06:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world line changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.65,0:06:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so she has no memory of sending that message.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.53,0:06:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you plan to attack the lab?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.03,0:06:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The IBN 5100 isn't there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.58,0:06:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.25,0:06:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.87,0:06:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.04,0:06:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've learned something you can't be allowed to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.59,0:06:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.34,0:06:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You made a time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.18,0:06:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.22,0:06:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to publicly announce it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.35,0:06:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew all that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.02,0:06:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does SERN know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My orders come from FB.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.45,0:06:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FB?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.70,0:06:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that an organization within SERN?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.66,0:07:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FB is everything to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.79,0:07:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where am I?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.29,0:07:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.45,0:07:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you John Titor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.80,0:07:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only person it could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.43,0:07:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.02,0:07:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.15,0:07:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bomb threat has halted all the trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.69,0:07:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to plan. {TL Note: keikaku means plan}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.99,0:07:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Capture Makise Kurisu and Hashida Itaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.87,0:07:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one else is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.41,0:07:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.54,0:07:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.54,0:07:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't kill Mayuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.63,0:07:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.42,0:08:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never wanted to expose SERN!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.22,0:08:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you the time leap machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.30,0:08:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never tell anyone what I learned!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.60,0:08:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Begin the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.18,0:08:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! I'll do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.35,0:08:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please... It was just simple curiosity...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.23,0:08:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a game!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.36,0:08:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... Just spare Mayuri...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.15,0:08:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.03,0:08:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.37,0:08:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.75,0:08:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.00,0:08:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.47,0:08:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.32,0:09:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.95,0:09:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you napping?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.70,0:09:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.96,0:09:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take this anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.21,0:09:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.75,0:09:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.42,0:09:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.21,0:09:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We decided we aren't doing the time leap.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.72,0:09:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you, all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.68,0:09:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going shopping, for the party, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.98,0:09:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The party...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.60,0:09:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Okabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.94,0:09:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the bullet train!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.03,0:09:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the bullet train is white.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.03,0:09:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oka... Kyouma-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.62,0:09:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Mayuri?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.00,0:09:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri-chan already left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.08,0:09:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.00,0:09:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know she came to invite you to the party...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.25,0:10:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that she's going to meet her friend who cosplays...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.93,0:10:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know she's looking forward to the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.30,0:10:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.19,0:10:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,900)}But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.73,0:10:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.91,0:10:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.79,0:10:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.50,0:10:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first time you've ever called me by the right name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.34,0:10:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.46,0:10:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, what's going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.63,0:10:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You time leaped, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.43,0:10:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.72,0:10:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.22,0:10:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.35,0:10:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:11:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never should have told Daru to hack into SERN.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.36,0:11:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never should have said to make the time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.44,0:11:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never should have invited Moeka to be a lab member!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.45,0:11:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault... And Mayuri...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.54,0:11:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pushing yourself too hard, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.96,0:11:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know that the time leap machine is completely safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.88,0:11:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible you could completely erase yourself from existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.93,0:11:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On a fundamental level, humans are temporal creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.97,0:11:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heidegger... I was just about to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.73,0:11:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned that phrase from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.73,0:11:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's kind of creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.06,0:11:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like you're peeking inside my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.44,0:11:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess that's what a time leap is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.82,0:11:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.66,0:11:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When will the lab be attacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.66,0:11:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After 7:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.95,0:12:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can think of several possible causes for Mayuri's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.63,0:12:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't have time to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.84,0:12:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.38,0:12:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri's a dear friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.18,0:12:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to save her, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.05,0:12:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.97,0:12:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.02,0:12:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.02,0:12:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.23,0:12:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mad scientist!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.77,0:12:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to change the world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.69,0:12:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.76,0:12:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set the time to five or so hours ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.10,0:12:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to just when the time leap machine was created.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you go to before it's completed, it's possible I won't finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You go back in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.94,0:13:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and once the time leap machine is done,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,send everyone away and tell me what we just discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.74,0:13:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say you've come from the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.37,0:13:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll probably believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.08,0:13:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.79,0:13:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know myself better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.79,0:13:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who made the time leap machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.13,0:13:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.05,0:13:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you're confident about your work?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.63,0:13:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.88,0:13:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I saw you back there, I was certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.80,0:13:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That you'd time leaped, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.06,0:13:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case, let's decide on a keyword.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.64,0:13:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, what I want most is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.73,0:13:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my own personal fork.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.11,0:13:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fork?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.19,0:13:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I already have a personal spoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.07,0:13:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be nosy about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.28,0:13:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.79,0:14:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.87,0:14:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five hours ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.17,0:14:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't remember that you called me Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.72,0:14:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you could hold this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.27,0:14:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.23,0:14:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.06,0:14:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it spread out like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.07,0:14:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That ribbon's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.44,0:14:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to try it on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.82,0:14:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still have some cosplay outfits for Comima.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.28,0:14:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cosplay, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.74,0:14:42.91,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.91,0:14:44.71,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.37,0:14:47.46,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't wear this around others...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.25,0:14:50.79,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.79,0:14:54.38,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Five hours ago, Mayuri hasn't left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.38,0:14:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I recall, her cosplay outfit's finished right as the time leap machine's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.43,0:15:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.35,0:15:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.10,0:15:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.77,0:15:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.56,0:15:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we're almost done, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.52,0:15:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.65,0:15:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.40,0:15:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't do the experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.99,0:15:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Darn... Was that too sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.91,0:15:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.45,0:15:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're all tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.12,0:15:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're done for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.25,0:15:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take a plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.30,0:15:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.55,0:15:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd just ordered when I got your message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.26,0:15:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think you were a regular here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not a regular!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.27,0:15:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri told me about this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.27,0:15:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what did you want to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.73,0:15:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You told us all to leave, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.94,0:15:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you suddenly message me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.61,0:15:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.78,0:16:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come from five hours in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.16,0:16:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's the stupidest line I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! That isn't what you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.54,0:16:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you'd probably believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.71,0:16:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.88,0:16:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably? Believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.46,0:16:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say anything that illogical.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.67,0:16:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.17,0:16:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm the one who made the time leap machine, to begin with."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.84,0:16:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You looked really proud, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.51,0:16:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a moron?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.01,0:16:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.48,0:16:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really want to smack her...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.19,0:16:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, what you want most is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.28,0:16:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your own personal fork.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.69,0:16:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.53,0:16:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.70,0:16:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The five-hours-from-now me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.24,0:16:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you already had your own spoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.91,0:16:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screw you, future me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.21,0:16:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You believe me now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.34,0:16:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... So the machine works just as I predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.71,0:17:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.18,0:17:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.22,0:17:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.72,0:17:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If all that's true, it's really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.93,0:17:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.19,0:17:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than help Mayuri escape, \Nhave you tried stopping Moeka-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.19,0:17:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Rounder, you called her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.81,0:17:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stopping her group and her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.36,0:17:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.07,0:17:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't stop Mayuri's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.91,0:17:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For something to occur, it must have a cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.79,0:17:32.29,Blackboard,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(296,471)\fr5\fry22}Cause
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.79,0:17:32.29,Blackboard,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(284,559)\fr5\fry22}Death
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.79,0:17:32.29,Blackboard,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(772,391)\fr5\fry22}Effect
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.29,0:17:34.42,Blackboard,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs120\pos(588,120)}Death
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, death would be preceded
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.88,0:17:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by some proximate phenomenon,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.01,0:17:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like an accident or an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.13,0:17:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't determine the cause for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.01,0:17:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Rounders are the proximate cause of Mayuri's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.18,0:17:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the real cause is likely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.60,0:17:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So even if the Rounders never appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.15,0:17:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri still dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:58.40,Blackboard,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(296,471)\fr5\fry22}Cause
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:58.40,Blackboard,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(284,560)\fr5\fry22}Death
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:58.40,Blackboard,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(772,391)\fr5\fry22}Effect
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what's the cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.69,0:17:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.90,0:18:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that the cause of Mayuri's death
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.32,0:18:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is Mayuri's own birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.66,0:18:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean her life span's run out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.20,0:18:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fatalism!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.12,0:18:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.91,0:18:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I won't suggest it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.04,0:18:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cause should be something
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.79,0:18:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that initiated this series of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.84,0:18:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Initiated...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.26,0:18:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible that if this isn't completed, Mayuri would...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.22,0:18:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.43,0:18:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous to jump to conclusions!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.89,0:18:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.06,0:18:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Makise Kurisu is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.31,0:18:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.73,0:18:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.02,0:18:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're more or less correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.48,0:18:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fixing everything won't be as easy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.78,0:18:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as not completing the time leap machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.36,0:18:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To save the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.45,0:18:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you need to reach world line beta.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.74,0:18:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must cross the 1% divergence barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.58,0:18:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The divergence number
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.46,0:19:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,indicates this world line's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.05,0:19:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only clue we have as to what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.34,0:19:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is this divergence meter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.22,0:19:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nixie Tubes? {D: TC - I couldn't find this name anywhere, and it's kind of weird. Anything you can dig up to verify? I think it's a future gadget he's not created yet}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.93,0:19:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever made it has good taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.72,0:19:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.22,0:19:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.43,0:19:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.77,0:19:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the power to retain
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.31,0:19:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your memories, when moving world lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.78,0:19:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the future, you made this meter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.24,0:19:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to numerically display
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.74,0:19:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the difference between this world line and the previous one you inhabited.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,0.337187...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.37,0:19:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's this world line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.75,0:19:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world line is like a woven braid or this rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.34,0:19:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This rope looks like it's a single line,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.18,0:19:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but actually, many thin threads comprise it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.47,0:19:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The threads are the world lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.64,0:19:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each never touches the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.56,0:20:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1054)}but they all go to the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.10,0:20:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.19,0:20:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they all tend toward a world in which Mayuri dies...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.74,0:20:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if the world line drastically changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.78,0:20:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from our alpha world line to the beta world line,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.24,0:20:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,over the 1% barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.12,0:20:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,another outcome would occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.87,0:20:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys use that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.96,0:20:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.96,0:20:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't climb up, just using that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.13,0:20:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.09,0:20:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.68,0:20:39.27,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is Amane-san, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.27,0:20:41.14,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,She's definitely a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.14,0:20:42.35,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Of some kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.57,0:20:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.78,0:20:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.82,0:20:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The alpha and beta world lines
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.45,0:20:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are world lines with completely different results.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:21:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, it's impossible to move between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.54,0:21:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you change the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.00,0:21:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,using the time leap and the D-mail,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.75,0:21:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.50,0:21:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in several years, major events occur,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.71,0:21:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the choices made then split the world into multiple world lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.93,0:21:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Recently, it would be 1991, when the Gulf War occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.56,0:21:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And 2000, with the Y2K problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.77,0:21:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And 2010, when the time machine was created.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.48,0:21:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.90,0:21:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the split occurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.99,0:21:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's possible to move from the alpha world line to the beta.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.91,0:21:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it done?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.87,0:21:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How{\fscx80}-
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.58,0:21:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.29,0:21:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.00,0:21:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tell us who are you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.47,0:21:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.22,0:21:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.81,0:22:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from the year 2036.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.27,0:22:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuha...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.39,0:22:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the time traveler
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.23,0:22:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,John Titor.

